  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: The governing requirement mandates experimental-validation as the verification method; however, the supporting validation activity was conducted as a numerical-simulation. The narrative presents the high-fidelity simulation as functionally equivalent to bench testing, but the structured activityType field records numerical-simulation rather than experimental-validation, breaking the formal inference link (W-AR-03).",
