      "name": "Hemolysis index validation — numerical simulation cross-check",
      "description": "Validation of CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) across five flow-speed operating points. The simulation team argues that the high-fidelity LES computation, using experimentally anchored boundary conditions from the FDA benchmark dataset, provides evidence equivalent to a dedicated bench experiment for the purposes of confirming RH < 1 at worst-case conditions. All five operating points yield RH < 1 in the simulation. The governing requirement (req/cpb-hemolysis-req-001) specifies experimental-validation as the required verification method; this result was instead produced by a numerical-simulation activity.",
