        "name": "High-fidelity LES simulation of FDA centrifugal pump hemolysis",
        "description": "Large-eddy simulation of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump at five flow-speed combinations (2.5 L/min at 2500 RPM, 3.5 L/min at 3500 RPM, 4.5 L/min at 3500 RPM, 5.5 L/min at 4500 RPM, 6.0 L/min at 4500 RPM). Mesh independence confirmed at 8.2M cells. Hemolysis power-law model (Giersiepen et al.) applied to Lagrangian particle tracks. Boundary conditions derived from published FDA benchmark experimental data. Simulation team asserts this constitutes functional experimental equivalence; however, no physical blood-loop bench test was conducted under this protocol.",
        "startedAtTime": "2025-11-01T08:00:00Z",
        "endedAtTime": "2025-12-15T17:00:00Z"
